# Visual scaling comparison
scaling_comparison: {
  label: "Scaling Comparison"
  direction: right
  full_scaling: {
    label: "Full State: O(N²)"
    bar_10: "████" {
      label: "10 nodes"
      style.fill: "#E57373"
      width: 40
    }
    bar_100: "████████████████████████████████████████" {
      label: "100 nodes"
      style.fill: "#EF5350"
      width: 200
    }
    bar_1000: "████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████" {
      label: "1000 nodes"
      style.fill: "#C62828"
      width: 400
      style.font-color: white
    }
  }
  delta_scaling: {
    label: "Delta: O(1)"
    delta_bar_10: "█" {
      label: "10 nodes"
      style.fill: "#81C784"
      width: 40
    }
    delta_bar_100: "█" {
      label: "100 nodes"
      style.fill: "#66BB6A"
      width: 40
    }
    delta_bar_1000: "█" {
      label: "1000 nodes"
      style.fill: "#4CAF50"
      width: 40
    }
  }
}
# Key insight annotation
insight: |md
  ## Key Insight
  **Full State Exchange:**
  - Sends entire state (S) to all N-1 peers
  - Bandwidth: O(N × S) per node per round
  - Does NOT scale - 1GB/round at 1000 nodes!
  **Delta-Based Gossip:**
  - Sends only changes (Δ) to fanout peers (k)
  - Bandwidth: O(k × Δ) - constant regardless of N
  - SCALES - same 3KB/round at any cluster size
  **Assumptions:**
  - State size (S) = 1MB per node
  - Delta size (Δ) = 1KB average
  - Fanout (k) = 3
| {near: bottom-center}
# Connections showing growth
cluster_10 -> cluster_100: "10× more nodes" {
  style.stroke: "#9E9E9E"
  style.stroke-dash: 3
}
cluster_100 -> cluster_1000: "10× more nodes" {
  style.stroke: "#9E9E9E"
  style.stroke-dash: 3
}
cluster_10 -> scaling_comparison.full_scaling
cluster_1000 -> scaling_comparison.delta_scaling